## Streaming Large Uploads in ASP.NET Core 8 Minimal API

`IFormFile` buffers the entire body into memory. Instead, read the multipart sections directly from the request stream using `MultipartReader`.

### 1. Disable request size limits

```csharp
// Program.cs
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
{
    o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024; // 2 GB
});

builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(k =>
{
    k.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

### 2. Stream to disk via `MultipartReader`

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    if (!request.HasFormContentType)
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected multipart/form-data");

    var boundary = request.GetMultipartBoundary();
    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(boundary))
        return Results.BadRequest("Missing boundary");

    var reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);
    MultipartSection? section;

    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
    {
        if (!ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(
                section.ContentDisposition, out var disposition)
            || !disposition.IsFileDisposition())
            continue;

        var fileName = Path.GetRandomFileName(); // sanitize!
        var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", fileName);

        await using var fileStream = File.Create(savePath);
        await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fileStream);
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();
```

### 3. Add the helper extension (already built-in)

`GetMultipartBoundary()` lives in `Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities`. Make sure you have:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities;
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;
```

### Why this works

| Approach | Memory usage | 2 GB file |
|----------|-------------|-----------|
| `IFormFile` | Buffers entire file | OOM ❌ |
| `MultipartReader` | ~80 KB buffer | Streams to disk ✅ |

`CopyToAsync` streams in small chunks (default 80 KB), so memory stays constant regardless of file size.

### Optional: progress & validation

- **Cap per-section size** — count bytes in a custom `CopyToAsync` loop and abort if exceeded.
- **Validate content type** — check `section.ContentType` before saving.
- **Antivirus scan** — scan the saved file before making it accessible.
